I also somehow hit the entity limit from too many lights so I had to delete half of them.... hmmm 

Enjoy :)

I wanted to make a map that could be played by players of most skill levels.

I decided to make a map that the player decides to play easy / mid / hard

The map is the same for each choice but depending on what skill the player chooses, depends on how they can play the map (it is not 3 copies of the map)

1.  Easy - the map is XC all blocks are available to the players. Long Jumps are disabled. No teleports on the blocks so the player can stand on every block
2. Mid - the map now becomes mpbhop for the player, the "white an00biz blocks" are not available to the player
3. Hard - The map now does not let the player pree-speed. Only 1 jump is allowed on each block, the player cannot go back 1 block. "white an00biz blocks" are not available to the player

Also I wanted other players to be able to tell which skill the player was on, so I coloured the player to denote the skill they chose. green=easy, blue=mid, red=hard.

The map has been tested on the ThC server & seems to work as designed, without bugs.

If you are a server owner then set up the timer to finish in the end room for "HARD", this will mean that the timer will only work for players on hard, other skills can still play but not finish the map as they will not be able to reach the finish room for "HARD". his makes it a map designed for Hard but available for other players to play instead of spectating or RTV.

inspired by aoki for pree-speed & 1 jump, but I made my own triggers, that work in a similar way, but with additional features.

I hope the triggers will inspire other mappers to make more friendly maps for all skill levels, instead of targetted at one skill.

Well at last I have finished the map, I have had fun making & playing the map, along with watching other people play the map

The end of the 1st map is very tight gaps, but once you have done it , you will be able to do it easier the next time you play, but don't give up you will do it.

There is a camera gun at the end of the 1st stage(red)  on the 2nd map, this can be seen throughout the maps on the monitors above the glass

On completing the map you can get on top of the glass & teleport round the map using the little coloured blocks, this can also take you back to the start

Overall difficulty is hard. Map is big.
Last level of each stage should be harder that usual.
Around map are occasionally helpers (signs, moving laser beam) which show you something useful (especially for newbies).

When you finish map, you can exchange your weapons in white square on the wall and you will get sign over your head and laser beam following you (in hidden stage there are different signs and color of beam you get every level you finish)
You can reset it in start room if you don't like it.

This map has taken way too long being in progress, this is because I procrastinated and had months where I didn't even open up hammer :(.

Features of the map:
- 9 shit-stained crappy mpbhop levels that you can prespeed grind your ass on.
- 88.4% brushsides (thanks to propper for that) that you can look at the shitty architecture on each stage with.
- A few jumps that require >400 vel.
- Very possible on legit.
- Auto rand friendly levels (mostly).
- Soundscapes for people to hate on.
- Compiled with HDR so your eyes can bleed out with the brightness.

Things I wish I'd done with the map:
- Bonus (couldn't fit).
- Better start/end room (couldn't fit).
- Better mapping.
- Less lazy mpbhops.
- Not hit about 4 limits in one.

Have fun and remember to RTV before those nerds in the server see the osu level.

(Hopefully I didn't fuck up the packing =D)

Changes in v2:
- Fixes for 4th/5th level skips.
- HDR less eyebleedingly bright (hopefully).
- The singular missing texture is now packed
